	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96682769718151><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=96682769718151>RE: Using your wizard in a group</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=96682769718151#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Aug 20th 11:14 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I support the idea of nuking towards the middle of a mob's life bar rather than towards the end or beginning.&nbsp;&nbsp;Many of your tanks have weapons that are procing as well as situations where some Cleric or Pali will cast a small nuke or Dot.  The thing is, trying to avoid corpse nuking, that is, thinking you are gonna get in the killing blow, only to end up frying something already dead--talk about a waste of mana!  On the other side of the situation, nuking too early leads to unnecessary resists and/or having the mob agro on you early in a combat round.  Since i don't yet have med/look ability, I usually stand, assits the primary tank while assesing the situations, including factors of what other group members are going to be able to contribute, then sit and med till I see the targeted mob's health is at about 70-80%.  Then I will add one major nuke.  If I don't get full dmg, I may add another lesser nuke--then I sit and med.  Depending on the area, particularly tight spaced dungeons, I may jump up on a mob near it's death and fry it if it is fleeing too close to places I know it's friends are waiting. Otherwise I try to avoid "Corpse Nukes" at all costs--they are just the worst waste of mana possible.<br><br>Another thought for groups is that if I see that the tanks are enganged heavily, and the healer gets agro'd, I will often throw a max nuke at that mob to get it off the healer.  The healer will usually then keep me healed while I either burn the mob, or some tank comes to pull it off me--or I just stun and root that mob and move to the other side of the battle to continue medding. If the mob returns on me, the tanks are usually in a better position by that time to taunt off me.<br><br>And yes, we need to get some AoE threads going here.  There are some awesome ones on Gaffes, but the topic is always worth keeping up, since some newer players may never find the old threads in this or other forums.<br><br><br>Kelvyn, 30th wiz, Veeshan<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
